The network is configured with the follwoing systems:
Windows 10 - TARGET-PC
Windows Server - Active Directory
Kali - Attacker 
Splunk Server

The project commences by bringing in the systems mentioned above on a single NAT network to ensure seamless communication. Windows Server acts as the domain controller for Active Directory, while Windows 10 
(TARGET-PC) simulates a client environment. Kali Linux is used for security testing, and Splunk provides centralized log monitoring. This is the setup for AD configuration.
Refer to the document for the entire workflow description of this attack.
